data.text:
2023-2024 - Points

Myles Cale scores a season high 30 points for Limburg United

On March 03, 2024, Myles Cale set a season high in points in a BNXT League game. That day he scored 30 points in Hubo Limburg United's road loss against Eiffel Towers Den Bosch, 95-86. He also had 6 rebounds, 5 assists, 1 steal and finished the game with a 32 efficiency.

2023-2024 - Rebounds

Jonas Delalieux grabs a season high 13 rebounds for Limburg United

On December 12, 2023, Jonas Delalieux set a season high in rebounds in a BNXT League game. That day he grabbed 13 rebounds in Hubo Limburg United's home win against Spirou Basket Charleroi, 76-55. He also had 10 points, 2 assists and finished the game with a 18 efficiency.

2023-2024 - Assists

Myles Cale dishes a season high 9 assists for Limburg United

On May 05, 2024, Myles Cale set a season high in assists in a BNXT League Playoffs game. That day he dished 9 assists in Hubo Limburg United's home win against Kangoeroes Basket Mechelen, 90-84. He also had 16 points, 5 rebounds, 5 steals and finished the game with a 23 efficiency.

2023-2024 - Steals

Myles Cale has a season high 5 steals for Limburg United

On May 05, 2024, Myles Cale set a season high in steals in a BNXT League Playoffs game. That day he reached 5 steals in Hubo Limburg United's home win against Kangoeroes Basket Mechelen, 90-84. He also had 16 points, 5 rebounds, 5 steals and finished the game with a 23 efficiency.

2023-2024 - Blocks

Osun Osunniyi blocks a season high 4 blocks for Limburg United Osun Osunniyi

On October 10, 2023, Osun Osunniyi set a season high in blocks in a BNXT League game. That day he went for 4 blocks in Hubo Limburg United's road win against Generali Okapi Aalstar, 82-83. He also had 14 points, 6 rebounds, 3 steals and finished the game with a 19 efficiency.

2023-2024 - Efficiency

Myles Cale set a season high 32 efficiency for Limburg United

On March 03, 2024, Myles Cale set a season high in efficiency in a BNXT League game. That day he accomplished 32 efficiency in Hubo Limburg United's road loss against Eiffel Towers Den Bosch, 95-86. He also had 30 points, 6 rebounds, 1 steal and finished the game with a 32 efficiency.
